The paper deals with machine learning algorithms for semi-supervised learning, specifically for optimizing AUC in nonlinear classification problems with kernels. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of kernels suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) applications. Additionally, since the paper deals with optimization algorithms, it may also be relevant to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
